                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/1969: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on Special Mission in Cuba</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-21T14:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 21, 1921—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. Reports thus far received from courts indicate necessity of special elections
                    on a scale which will place the choice of President in doubt. In conference held
                    this morning President Menocal expressed same view.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crowder</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
